years ago, however, while conducting a meditation retreat near Bear Creek Canyon in Colorado, I had the good fortune to see a phantom deer.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0  It should be explained that the site of this retreat was unusual in several ways. On the property are five of the \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 
largest blue spruces I have ever seen. They tower above all other trees in the area and are believed to be inhabited by a very high deva who watches over the property. Because of the presence of this spirit, it is known as a healing place and was known as
\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 such by the American Indians before the white man came.
\par 
