\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Later lying on the grass, lazily gazing up into the sky, I asked her, \'93\loch\f0 How did you know the bird was there, Lois? You cou\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 ldn't have heard it."
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 \hich\f0  She didn't answer for a while. She rolled over and gazed into the grass as though watching some occurrence. Then slowly, \'93\loch\f0 
As me, Lois, I could not see or hear the hawk, something apart and not of me. But, then, I release myself and \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
